column5: Do you mean Tobin Lake in Saskatchewan. If you do spoke with a friend that live in Nipawin and he said fishing was great only to get better in Sept.

Tobin has been very good most of this summer. As we get into fall the big pike should start and always good walleye in the river. Haven't heard about walleye on the lake but should be good for another month.
Yes Tobin Lake at nippawin. Headed that way soon.
